rComments: Best Prof I've had at UofT.  Makes you talk to him about your essay topic before you choose one, but your pretty much allowed to choose any topic within the subject.  Has his own psych practice and tells stories about his patients in order to illustrate the Freudian theories.  Very nice guy, smart and understanding.
I am looking forward to taking more courses next year. I loved this class!

Haartman shows great enthusiasm for the course material which was very infectious! He is always available to discuss the material outside of class. He provides clear examples and encourages students to think critically. I highly recommend taking any of his courses, you will love them!

Prof. Haartman is a phenomenal instructor.  His explanations and examples are clear and to the point.  He engages and challenges his students, encouraging discussion in class. What stands out most is his committment to his students - there was never a time when any question was left unanswered.

The professor expressed genunine interest and excitement over the material, which generated the same in students. He used many examples and humour, to facilitate learning. By far the most interesting course I've taken in a long time.
2002-2003 rated 100% RETAKE at UofT! 2000-2001 rated 81% RETAKE 2004-2005 rated #1 ...I could get into details, but you have to be in his class to know!
